headline: Principal Financial's profit rises on remeasurement gains; shares jump
summary: Shares of the company jumped 4.6% in after-hours trading.  Insurance companies set aside capital to cover payments they expect to make to policyholders in the future, based on existing insurance contracts.  A remeasurement gain happens when the company realizes it has set aside too much money and can reduce the liability.

headline: Principal Financial: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) — Principal Financial Group Inc. PFG) on Monday reported second-quarter profit of $406.2 million. On a per-share basis, the Des Moines, Iowa-based company said it had profit of $1.79.
